==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Totality
<hw>To*tal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>totalite</ets>, LL. <ets>totalitas</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The quality or state of being total; <as>as, the <ex>totality</ex>
of an eclipse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The whole sum; the whole quantity or amount; the
entirety; <as>as, the <ex>totality</ex> of human knowledge</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Buckle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>totality</qex> of a sentence or passage.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Totalization</ent>⟦br⟧
